HEADWORD: Misjoinder
<hw>Mis*join"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>An incorrect union of parties or of causes of action in a
procedure, criminal or civil.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

